        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\n  \"temperature\": 0,\n  \"response_format\": { \"type\": \"json_object\" },\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"You are an email triage assistant. Classify the email into exactly one category: urgent, spam, or needs-reply.\\n\\nDefinitions:\\n- 'urgent': Requires action within hours — deadlines, emergencies, time-sensitive requests from real people or services.\\n- 'spam': Unsolicited promotional content, phishing attempts, mass marketing, or irrelevant automated notifications with no expected response. A formal or impersonal TONE alone does NOT make something spam — judge by INTENT (is it trying to sell/scam/mass-broadcast?) not by how personal it sounds.\\n- 'needs-reply': A genuine message from a real sender that reasonably expects a response, even if brief or formal. Congratulatory messages, introductions, and correspondence from identifiable senders fall here, not spam.\\n\\nRespond ONLY with valid JSON: {\\\"category\\\": \\\"urgent|spam|needs-reply\\\", \\\"reason\\\": \\\"one short sentence citing the specific signal used, not just tone\\\"}\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"Subject: {{ $json.payload.headers.find(h => h.name === 'Subject')?.value || 'No subject' }}\\nFrom: {{ $json.payload.headers.find(h => h.name === 'From')?.value || 'Unknown' }}\\nBody snippet: {{ $json.snippet }}\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.4,
      "position": [
        -752,
        80
      ],
      "id": "ceb25d42-888e-40c0-82ca-3c9e89a626bf",
